11 Section 1. Section 2-15-3110, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "2-15-3110. Livestock loss board -- purpose, membership, and qualifications. (1) There is a
13 livestock loss board. The purpose of the board is to administer the programs called for in the Montana gray wolf
14 conservation and management plan, the Montana mountain lion management plan, the Montana black bear
15 management plan, and the Montana grizzly bear management plan and established in 2-15-3111 through 2-15-
16 3113, with funds provided through the accounts established in 81-1-110, in order to minimize losses caused by
17 wolves, mountain lions, black bears, and grizzly bears to livestock producers and to reimburse livestock
18 producers for livestock losses from wolf, mountain lion, black bear, and grizzly bear predation.
19 (2) The board consists of five members, appointed by the governor, as follows:
20 (a) three members who are actively involved in the livestock industry and who have knowledge
21 and experience with regard to wildlife impacts or management; and
22 (b) two members of the general public who are or have been actively involved in wildlife
23 conservation or wildlife management and who have knowledge and experience with regard to livestock
24 production or management.
25 (3) The board is designated as a quasi-judicial board for the purposes of 2-15-124.
26 Notwithstanding the provisions of 2-15-124(1), the governor is not required to appoint an attorney to serve as a
27 member of the board.
28 (4) The board is allocated to the department of livestock for administrative purposes only as
