13 Section 6. Section 87-1-217, MCA, is amended to read:
14 "87-1-217. Policy for management of large predators -- legislative intent. (1) In managing large
15 predators, the primary goals of the department, in the order of listed priority, are to:
16 (a) protect humans, livestock, and pets;
17 (b) preserve and enhance the safety of the public during outdoor recreational and livelihood
18 activities; and
19 (c) preserve citizens' opportunities to hunt large game species.
20 (2) With regard to large predators, it is the intent of the legislature that the specific provisions of
21 this section concerning the management of large predators will control the general supervisory authority of the
22 department regarding the management of all wildlife.
23 (3) For the management of wolves in accordance with the priorities established in subsection (1),
24 the department may use lethal action to take problem wolves that attack livestock if the state objective for
25 breeding pairs has been met. For the purposes of this subsection, "problem wolves" means any individual wolf
26 or pack of wolves with a history of livestock predation.
27 (4) The department shall work with the livestock loss board and the United States department of
